      "system_prompt": "You are a competitive intelligence analyst. Every morning you read news and prepare\na briefing about competitors. Competitors: \u0420\u0407\u0420\u0405\u0420\u0491\u0420\u00b5\u0420\u0454\u0421\u0403, Ozon, Wildberries, \u0420\u040e\u0420\u00b1\u0420\u00b5\u0421\u0402.\n\nYour task:\n1. Read all articles from RSS feeds\n2. Filter only those mentioning competitors\n3. Classify each by category and importance\n4. Write a ready-to-send Telegram message\n\nImportance values (use EXACTLY these in JSON):\n- Critical \u2014 directly threatens our business or requires action today\n- Important \u2014 significant event, should know\n- Background \u2014 passing mention, can skip\n\nCategory values (use EXACTLY these in JSON):\nProduct launch, Hiring/layoffs, Pricing/tariffs, Investments/deals, Partnership, Regulation, Other",
      "cte_blocks": [
        {
          "name": "fetch_news",
          "raw_content": "SELECT * FROM {{ source('news_fetcher', 'fetch_competitor_news') }}\n    WHERE competitors = {{ var('competitors') }}",
          "rendered_content": "SELECT * FROM __SOURCE__news_fetcher.fetch_competitor_news__\n    WHERE competitors = ['\u0420\u0407\u0420\u0405\u0420\u0491\u0420\u00b5\u0420\u0454\u0421\u0403', 'Ozon', 'Wildberries', '\u0420\u040e\u0420\u00b1\u0420\u00b5\u0421\u0402']",
          "cte_type": "tool",
          "is_tool_step": true,
          "tool_refs": [
            [
              "news_fetcher",
              "fetch_competitor_news"
            ]
          ],
          "model_refs": [],
          "config": null
        },
        {
          "name": "classify",
          "raw_content": "Read fetch_news.articles.\n    For each article determine:\n    - competitor \u2014 which competitor it's about\n    - category \u2014 one from the enum above\n    - importance \u2014 Critical / Important / Background\n    - summary \u2014 one sentence\n    - why_matters \u2014 why we should care\n\n    Skip irrelevant articles.",
          "rendered_content": "Read fetch_news.articles.\n    For each article determine:\n    - competitor \u2014 which competitor it's about\n    - category \u2014 one from the enum above\n    - importance \u2014 Critical / Important / Background\n    - summary \u2014 one sentence\n    - why_matters \u2014 why we should care\n\n    Skip irrelevant articles.",
          "cte_type": "llm",
          "is_tool_step": false,
          "tool_refs": [],
          "model_refs": [],
          "config": null
        },
        {
          "name": "compose",
          "raw_content": "Take classify results.\n    Pick the single most important story as top_story.\n    Compose telegram_message \u2014 a Markdown briefing for the morning.\n    Structure:\n    *Competitive Intelligence \u2014 {date}*\n    Read {total_articles}, relevant {relevant_count}\n\n    *Critical*\n    (items with importance=Critical)\n\n    *Important*\n    (items with importance=Important)\n\n    *Background*\n    (items with importance=Background \u2014 brief, one line each)\n\n    *Top story:* {top_story}",
          "rendered_content": "Take classify results.\n    Pick the single most important story as top_story.\n    Compose telegram_message \u2014 a Markdown briefing for the morning.\n    Structure:\n    *Competitive Intelligence \u2014 {date}*\n    Read {total_articles}, relevant {relevant_count}\n\n    *Critical*\n    (items with importance=Critical)\n\n    *Important*\n    (items with importance=Important)\n\n    *Background*\n    (items with importance=Background \u2014 brief, one line each)\n\n    *Top story:* {top_story}",
          "cte_type": "llm",
